I took this class in 6 months ago and i still have nightmares up until now about it

rComments: This guy is a grade A tool. Enough said...

This guy only cares about his image lool, check his rate my prof comments. The ones that are 5 for quality are written by him. He literally has word for word the same comments on uOttawa rate my prof and his University of Quebec one. There's a testament about his character and teaching quality.

Professor George is awesome. What I like the most is the absence of surprise. He told us from the beginning not to expect this course to be easy if we are arab. His comments on papers are very long and very clear. He offers to meet us anytime on adobe connect, even weekend. To be sure, this course is not for lazy ones, but OMG how much I learned.

I took 3 courses with him, language, culture & literature. I regret there are no more which I can take with him. His knowledge and the way he explains are excellent. In large classes he is a bit strict, to maintain discipline I guess, but in normal classes he is very gentile and funny. Always available in person or by phone, evening, weekends, etc.

The class itself was enjoyable, and I didn't really mind the quizzes at the end of each lecture. However, the final exam was extremely poorly written. It barely covers the contents of the notes you take (and you take a lot of notes!). Instead, it focuses on a huge novel that's extremely long and hard to read, and he expects details from it. Avoid!

Great teacher, knows subject very well. Most of the course was online and about 4 lectures was in class. Every lecture has a quiz at the end. He expects you to read 15 chapters of a big fat book with the font size of 3pt... His exams are somewhat hard and an easy marker for essays. He makes class time interesting
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Pretty good prof ... interesting content and he makes it more so by showing lots of pictures and videos. Wouldn't jump at the chance to be in his class again but I also would't be upset if it happened.
